+# resume_project
+
+Minimal node server added to make the repository runnable and fix `npm start` ENOENT.
+
+## What was added
+- `package.json` — minimal scripts: `start` and `dev`.
+- `server.js` — tiny HTTP server to verify the project runs.
+- `.gitignore` — common ignores.
+- `README.md` — this file.
+
+## How to run locally
+1. Clone the repo (if not already):
+
+```bash
+git clone https://github.com/aryantechworld2019-gif/resume_project.git
+cd resume_project
+```
+
+2. Create branch, apply patch (or if you used the provided patch file, see instructions in repo root).
+
+3. Install (no deps required for this minimal server):
+
+```bash
+npm install
+npm start
+```
+
+4. Open `http://localhost:3000` — you should see `resume_project is running`.
+
